                            content.</draft-comment>The maximum transmission unit for the interface.
                        For more information, see <ph ixia_locid="274" otherprops="printonly"><cite ixia_locid="241">Titanium Server Planning: </cite></ph><cite ixia_locid="275"><ph ixia_locid="276"><xref href="jow1404333732592.xml" ixia_locid="277"/></ph></cite>.</p>
                    <note id="note_N10274_N1024F_N10246_N10012_N1000F_N10001" ixia_locid="296">
                        <p ixia_locid="297"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="298">CGTS-4671</draft-comment>You cannot change the MTU for an
                            infrastructure interface. The value from the network resource is always
                            used.</p>
                    </note>
                </dd>
            </dlentry>
            <dlentry ixia_locid="53">
                <dt ixia_locid="54">IPv4 Addressing Mode</dt>
